    "body": "Add fused FC1 GEMM + SwiGLU activation kernels for shared experts in DeepSeek-V3 with NVFP4 quantization, producing both BF16 and FP4 output variants.\r\n\r\nPerf result on GB200 1k/1k 1ctx + 2gen DEP8 bs512 DeepSeek-FP4 tps/user:\r\nbefore fusion : 24.37 tok/s\r\nafter fusion : 25.24 tok/s\r\n~3.5% perf improvement\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n\r\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\r\n\r\n## Release Notes\r\n\r\n* **New Features**\r\n  * Added CuTe DSL NVFP4 support with SwiGLU fusion optimization for Blackwell GPUs\r\n  * Introduced `--use_cute_dsl_blockscaling_mm` command-line flag for enabling advanced kernel fusion\r\n  * Added FP4 output path variant for SwiGLU fusion operations\r\n  * Implemented fused gated MLP path leveraging SwiGLU kernel acceleration\r\n\r\n* **Tests**\r\n  * Added integration tests validating CuTe DSL NVFP4 with SwiGLU fusion across single and multi-GPU configurations\r\n  * Added validation scripts for dense GEMM SwiGLU fusion kernel behavior and performance\r\n\r\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
